                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#94rc">f. 94rc</locus>
                           <desc>: Record concerning a litigation in the court over an alleged
                              murder.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#94rc">94rc</locus>: በ፲ወ፱፻፲ወ፱ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ጊዜውን፡ በራስ፡
                              ሥዩም፡ ጊዜ፡ ነው፡ ቄስ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ቄስ፡ ገብረ፡ ጻድቃን፡ ከሳስኪ[sic]፡ አቶ፡ ደስታ፡ ተከሻሽ፡
                              እኅትየን፡ ገድልከልኝ፡ ብለው፡ ከሰሱት[sic]፡ እኔ፡ አልገደልኩም፡ ብሎ፡ ከሰንሰለት፡ ገባ፡ ከደጃዝማች፡
                              ደስታ፡ ችኰት፡ ቀረቡ፡ …</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> The record was written in Amharic in 1919 year of
                           mercy (= 1926/27 A.D.) during the time of rās Sǝyyum Mängäša (govenor of
                           Tǝgray in 1914-60). The priests Takla Hāymānot and Gabra Ṣādǝqān accuse
                              ʾato<note> Dästa to have murdered their sister, they went to the court
                              of däǧǧazmač Dästa to settle the dispute. The judges were lǝğ Kidānu,
                              šäqa Ḫǝdāru and Baḥǝta Sǝkus. Further in the note it is mentioned that
                              they should swear an oath on Gunda Gunde (here written Gʷǝngʷǝnde) to
                              prove their innocence. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Spacea for the rubricated name of the owner left
                           unfilled throughout the Ms.
 - An additional (or overlooked?)
                           ʾarke-hymn is added to the 23rd Miyāzyā: <locus target="#42vc">42vc</locus>.
 - Ownership note in Amharic written in a recent
                           secondary hand, modern blue pen in the margin: <locus target="#72v">72v</locus> ይሕ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ስንክሣር፡ የበዓቲ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ነው፡
 - The name of
                           Walatta ʾIyasus is written in a recent secondary hand, in blue pen:
                              <locus target="#138rb">138rb</locus>.
 - Pen trail: <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>. 
 - Omitted (?) passages written in the
                           margin: <locus target="#72r">72r</locus>, 87v, 92v, 144v.
 -
                           Scribbles: <locus target="#77r">77r</locus>, 151r.
 - A illegible
                           note in pencil: <locus target="#152v">152v</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
